WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.370 --> 00:00:03.570
Extend your hand, no need to fear

3
00:00:03.780 --> 00:00:06.740
Cut through the wind, and persevere

4
00:00:07.070 --> 00:00:11.410
Chart your own course, the time to push forward is here

5
00:00:16.390 --> 00:00:19.710
In a time like a storm, hear the tidal waves roar,

6
00:00:19.710 --> 00:00:22.750
we keep trudging along but we're still wanting more

7
00:00:22.960 --> 00:00:26.260
But in spite of it all, the foundation we built

8
00:00:26.260 --> 00:00:28.880
for ourselves was about to fall

9
00:00:29.470 --> 00:00:32.760
Where the compass points - Is it right? Is it wrong?

10
00:00:32.760 --> 00:00:35.470
Who to ask? As if there's anyone listening

11
00:00:35.830 --> 00:00:38.810
I guess you'll never be one hundred percent sure

12
00:00:39.310 --> 00:00:42.270
But if you shut your eyes to the chaos,

13
00:00:42.560 --> 00:00:45.400
and you'd only take a breath

14
00:00:45.820 --> 00:00:48.700
When you open up your eyes

15
00:00:49.070 --> 00:00:52.410
you will find where you were meant to be

16
00:00:52.780 --> 00:00:55.830
Extend your hand, no need to fear

17
00:00:55.990 --> 00:00:59.040
Cut through the wind, and persevere

18
00:00:59.310 --> 00:01:03.920
Kick out the dark until the sky clears

19
00:01:05.210 --> 00:01:08.090
Even as we act in our own best interests,

20
00:01:08.260 --> 00:01:11.930
doing what we each believe is for our own

21
00:01:12.390 --> 00:01:16.720
Chart your own course, the time to push forward is here

22
00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:33.660
I don't believe it!

23
00:01:33.700 --> 00:01:40.200
<b>Leader of the Mt. Atama Thieves,
Ashura Doji</b>

24
00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:36.200
The Oniwabanshu captains...

25
00:01:36.490 --> 00:01:38.660
and the Mimawari-gumi's, too...

26
00:01:38.660 --> 00:01:40.830
Most of them are down!

27
00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:42.040
Daikoku!

28
00:01:42.580 --> 00:01:43.880
Lord Kazekage!

29
00:01:43.880 --> 00:01:45.790
Captain Hotei!

30
00:01:49.340 --> 00:01:52.380
So that's what the legendary
yakuza is capable of, huh?!

31
00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:56.680
He resisted the effects of the ice ogre,
but still took advantage of its power!

32
00:01:57.100 --> 00:01:59.890
I think I'm beginning to understand...

33
00:02:01.230 --> 00:02:03.190
why Wano has been so feared...

34
00:02:11.110 --> 00:02:12.950
Boss!

35
00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:17.410
Boss Hyogoro!

36
00:02:19.990 --> 00:02:22.830
What are you waiting for, Yatappe?!

37
00:02:26.080 --> 00:02:28.340
Empty your mind!

38
00:02:28.880 --> 00:02:31.630
If I turn into an ice ogre...

39
00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:38.510
I know!

40
00:02:38.510 --> 00:02:40.310
Just give me a second!

41
00:02:40.310 --> 00:02:42.140
I'm gonna do it!

42
00:02:42.140 --> 00:02:44.390
I'll do it right now!

43
00:02:46.650 --> 00:02:48.270
Of course it's difficult...

44
00:02:48.980 --> 00:02:50.730
After all, that man...

45
00:02:50.730 --> 00:02:52.740
is like a father to us!

46
00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:00.950
Tsunagoro, cut me down right now!

47
00:03:01.990 --> 00:03:04.580
Boss Hyogoro...

48
00:03:04.580 --> 00:03:06.460
I'll join you soon!

49
00:03:11.710 --> 00:03:13.210
Omasa!

50
00:03:13.210 --> 00:03:14.720
Dammit!

51
00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:18.050
Isn't there any way you can
finish in time, Mr. Tanuki?!

52
00:03:18.050 --> 00:03:19.890
I can't fight it anymore, either!

53
00:03:19.890 --> 00:03:21.640
There's no saving me now!

54
00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:25.640
Just do it!

55
00:03:26.140 --> 00:03:27.900
Don't let me...

56
00:03:28.520 --> 00:03:30.270
Boss Omasa!

57
00:03:32.360 --> 00:03:36.110
Don't let me hurt you all!

58
00:03:36.110 --> 00:03:37.910
Mr. Tanuki!

59
00:03:37.910 --> 00:03:39.780
Surely the cure is ready by now?!

60
00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:42.700
The entire floor...

61
00:03:43.370 --> 00:03:44.620
all of our companions...

62
00:03:45.250 --> 00:03:47.960
will succumb to the ice ogre once more!

63
00:03:52.130 --> 00:03:56.670
Your Awesomeness!

64
00:03:57.090 --> 00:04:02.430
We work for you, man... Why do we
have to die from your virus, too?!

65
00:04:08.100 --> 00:04:11.360
Shut your mouths, you lowlifes!

66
00:04:11.360 --> 00:04:16.280
You punks have outlived your usefulness!

67
00:04:17.030 --> 00:04:18.700
Listen up!

68
00:04:18.700 --> 00:04:22.120
If I can't use you, you're as good as trash!

69
00:04:28.460 --> 00:04:32.130
The ice ogre virus is my
crowning achievement!

70
00:04:32.130 --> 00:04:36.170
If anything, it was made especially for you!

71
00:04:36.590 --> 00:04:38.760
Hey, Pleasures!

72
00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:43.890
You guys already lost the ability lottery!

73
00:04:43.890 --> 00:04:47.060
Now you're nothing but
cackling cannon fodder!

74
00:04:47.060 --> 00:04:48.600
Th-That's awful!

75
00:04:50.310 --> 00:04:52.690
Hey, Waiters!

76
00:04:52.690 --> 00:04:56.860
You can wait all you like, but there're
no more smile fruits coming!

77
00:04:56.860 --> 00:05:00.280
You guys lost your chance to be somebody!

78
00:05:00.280 --> 00:05:03.240
The Eternal Waiters.

79
00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:06.370
It's a fitting name, since all you can do is wait!

80
00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:12.120
The only way you layabouts can
be of use to the mighty Beast Pirates...

81
00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:14.960
is by at least becoming
an ogre before you die.

82
00:05:14.960 --> 00:05:18.460
That way you can do something
worth a damn with your final moments!

83
00:05:19.220 --> 00:05:22.260
So are you saying... we should just die?!

84
00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:24.510
Oh! Now you get it!

85
00:05:26.390 --> 00:05:29.520
We already have plenty of troops.

86
00:05:30.430 --> 00:05:32.560
What an awful thing to say!

87
00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:33.730
No way...

88
00:05:33.730 --> 00:05:35.820
You had your chance!

89
00:05:35.820 --> 00:05:39.360
Those antibodies could still save some of you!

90
00:05:44.660 --> 00:05:47.580
Dammit! I'm not gonna die without a fight!

91
00:05:47.580 --> 00:05:51.580
Cut down every ice ogre,
samurai and allies alike!

92
00:05:54.330 --> 00:05:56.000
Now that's what I'm talkin' about!

93
00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.840
Fight your asses off to survive!

94
00:05:59.340 --> 00:06:02.590
His treatment of his men is sickening!

95
00:06:02.590 --> 00:06:04.220
Indeed it is.

96
00:06:04.550 --> 00:06:06.470
Hey, you damn samurai!

97
00:06:06.470 --> 00:06:11.600
Maybe you don't realize
who you're protecting over there,

98
00:06:11.600 --> 00:06:14.020
but in case you forgot, that tanuki...

99
00:06:14.650 --> 00:06:16.980
is a pirate, just like us!

100
00:06:18.110 --> 00:06:19.610
Queen...

101
00:06:19.610 --> 00:06:23.570
Synthesizing that many antibodies
in such a short amount of time?!

102
00:06:25.700 --> 00:06:26.910
Don't make me laugh!

103
00:06:26.910 --> 00:06:32.460
He probably just gave himself
the cure and bailed!

104
00:06:33.830 --> 00:06:36.420
He's nothing like you villains!

105
00:06:37.590 --> 00:06:39.420
Are you sure about that?

106
00:06:39.420 --> 00:06:42.090
Pirates aren't known for being loyal!

107
00:06:46.090 --> 00:06:48.510
Boss Hyogoro!

108
00:06:48.510 --> 00:06:51.470
I'll be right behind you!

109
00:06:53.850 --> 00:06:56.400
Don't be so hasty to follow me...

110
00:07:02.190 --> 00:07:04.530
– Big Boss!
– Big Boss!

111
00:07:09.410 --> 00:07:11.120
Farewell...

112
00:07:19.790 --> 00:07:22.380
Wait!

113
00:07:33.020 --> 00:07:35.810
Don't try and stop me, Mr. Tanuki!

114
00:07:35.810 --> 00:07:38.150
We have no other choice!

115
00:07:38.560 --> 00:07:39.810
Just wait!

116
00:07:39.810 --> 00:07:41.480
I'll save him right now!

117
00:07:42.940 --> 00:07:45.110
Boss! Swallow it!

118
00:07:50.030 --> 00:07:52.490
Thank goodness! We made it just in time!

119
00:07:54.040 --> 00:07:56.250
B-Boss...

120
00:08:00.250 --> 00:08:02.750
Alright! It's working!

121
00:08:02.750 --> 00:08:04.590
Your body is warming up!

122
00:08:21.150 --> 00:08:22.980
Boss Hyogoro!

123
00:08:22.980 --> 00:08:24.570
Are you all right?!

124
00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:26.820
Yeah...

125
00:08:31.490 --> 00:08:32.620
It worked!

126
00:08:32.620 --> 00:08:34.950
I knew you could do it, Mr. Tanuki!

127
00:08:36.750 --> 00:08:39.370
Miyagi! Tristan! On the double!

128
00:08:41.130 --> 00:08:43.290
Right away, Dr. Chopper!

129
00:08:44.420 --> 00:08:45.840
What's that?

130
00:08:50.340 --> 00:08:53.010
It's all set, Dr. Chopper!

131
00:08:53.010 --> 00:08:55.470
Alright! Let's do it!

132
00:08:59.350 --> 00:09:01.980
Dr. Chopper! Just give the order!

133
00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:03.270
– A cannon?!
– A cannon?!

134
00:09:04.150 --> 00:09:06.690
Chopperphage...

135
00:09:06.690 --> 00:09:08.990
Nebulizer!

136
00:09:08.820 --> 00:09:10.740
<b>N
E
B
U
L
I
Z
E
R</b>
<b>C
H
O
P
P
E
R
P
H
A
G
E</b>

137
00:09:10.740 --> 00:09:12.780
Fire!

138
00:09:31.550 --> 00:09:35.100
Everyone! Inhale the mist!

139
00:09:36.760 --> 00:09:41.060
What do you think you're
doing, you damn tanuki?!

140
00:09:43.020 --> 00:09:48.650
The pinnacle of my work...
What have you done!?

141
00:09:51.400 --> 00:09:57.490
Individually handing out medicine to thousands
of soldiers would be impossible!

142
00:09:57.910 --> 00:10:02.000
So I created my own virus
using the antibodies!

143
00:10:02.410 --> 00:10:03.790
You what?!

144
00:10:04.130 --> 00:10:07.170
A good virus can counteract a bad virus!

145
00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:13.260
This way, everyone just needs
to breathe in the mist to be cured!

146
00:10:15.180 --> 00:10:18.760
You're just some ship doctor
from a backwater pirate crew...

147
00:10:18.760 --> 00:10:21.560
Where did you learn something like this?!

148
00:10:21.560 --> 00:10:24.850
We scattered all over the world
to train for moments like this!

149
00:10:24.850 --> 00:10:29.400
You even cured my own guys of ice ogre!

150
00:10:29.400 --> 00:10:31.650
What gives you the right?!

151
00:10:32.950 --> 00:10:36.740
Who in their right mind
would use a virus as a weapon?!

152
00:10:36.740 --> 00:10:39.540
There's no way to control it!

153
00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:48.090
I am not gonna be lectured on
ethics by a damn tanuki!

154
00:10:48.090 --> 00:10:50.750
Who the hell do you take me for?!

155
00:11:01.220 --> 00:11:02.930
Pleasures?!

156
00:11:04.480 --> 00:11:05.480
Why?!

157
00:11:08.060 --> 00:11:10.110
What the hell are you doing?!

158
00:11:10.110 --> 00:11:12.690
Stay out of this, you rats!

159
00:11:12.690 --> 00:11:14.490
Up yours, Queen!

160
00:11:15.450 --> 00:11:18.870
You nearly killed our brothers...

161
00:11:18.870 --> 00:11:21.700
but Mr. Tanuki here saved our asses!

162
00:11:22.700 --> 00:11:26.790
We'd rather die side-by-side
with the guy who saved us...

163
00:11:26.790 --> 00:11:29.960
instead of being killed
by our crazy-ass boss!

164
00:11:29.960 --> 00:11:32.460
Ain't that right, boys?!

165
00:11:35.590 --> 00:11:37.430
Thank you, tanuki!

166
00:11:37.430 --> 00:11:42.680
Tanuki!

167
00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:45.730
We are in your debt,
Mr. Tanuki!

168
00:11:46.100 --> 00:11:48.190
Mr. Tanuki... Thank you!

169
00:11:48.190 --> 00:11:51.520
You're really somethin' else,
little tanuki.

170
00:11:51.860 --> 00:12:01.450
– Tanuki! Tanuki! Tanuki! Tanuki!
– Tanuki! Tanuki! Tanuki! Tanuki!

171
00:12:01.450 --> 00:12:03.790
Go to hell, Queen!

172
00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:10.580
You little shits!

173
00:12:13.460 --> 00:12:16.130
What the hell is this?!

174
00:12:16.550 --> 00:12:18.510
Not bad at all, tanuki!

175
00:12:20.010 --> 00:12:21.300
Now let him have it.

176
00:12:21.680 --> 00:12:23.560
Thanks, Marco!

177
00:12:23.560 --> 00:12:25.980
There's just one more thing that I wanna say!

178
00:12:25.980 --> 00:12:29.020
Tanuki!

179
00:12:29.770 --> 00:12:30.980
Rumble!

180
00:12:31.520 --> 00:12:33.860
Monster Point!

181
00:12:34.650 --> 00:12:37.280
– Get him!
– Get him!

182
00:12:36.030 --> 00:12:37.280
You got this!

183
00:12:38.070 --> 00:12:39.030
What?!

184
00:12:40.740 --> 00:12:50.080
I'm not a tanuki!

185
00:12:46.790 --> 00:12:50.080
We're so sorry!

186
00:12:50.250 --> 00:12:53.380
<b>Right-Brain Tower

Inside the Dome</b>

187
00:12:53.380 --> 00:12:56.960
There's a bunch of space between
each floor of the castle!

188
00:12:56.960 --> 00:12:58.590
No one'll see us there!

189
00:12:58.590 --> 00:12:59.800
Okay!

190
00:12:59.800 --> 00:13:03.180
Lord Momonosuke! Please hold on
just a little longer!

191
00:13:03.600 --> 00:13:06.310
Momonosuke, are you okay?

192
00:13:07.390 --> 00:13:09.770
I am not okay...

193
00:13:14.230 --> 00:13:15.980
What do you mean?!

194
00:13:16.860 --> 00:13:20.070
I am not okay. I feel awful.

195
00:13:20.530 --> 00:13:22.610
I hate myself.

196
00:13:24.410 --> 00:13:27.200
Everyone gives me too much credit!

197
00:13:28.450 --> 00:13:30.960
I... I...

198
00:13:34.920 --> 00:13:38.800
I am frivolous, stupid...

199
00:13:38.800 --> 00:13:42.930
weak, foolish, and I make myself sick...

200
00:13:42.930 --> 00:13:45.300
Lord Momonosuke, I think you're amazing!

201
00:13:46.810 --> 00:13:48.770
I am not amazing at all!

202
00:13:48.770 --> 00:13:50.600
Even if you're small now,

203
00:13:51.060 --> 00:13:56.610
I know that you'll grow up to
be a proper shogun one day!

204
00:13:56.610 --> 00:14:00.690
You'll be an even greater man
than Kozuki Oden ever was!

205
00:14:03.360 --> 00:14:06.950
I am not... I am not...

206
00:14:09.950 --> 00:14:12.250
I am not amazing at all!

207
00:14:12.960 --> 00:14:14.540
What?!

208
00:14:14.540 --> 00:14:15.790
An eel?!

209
00:14:15.790 --> 00:14:17.540
Lord Momonosuke!

210
00:14:18.670 --> 00:14:20.920
Why do you look like that?

211
00:14:21.550 --> 00:14:27.140
This is what happens to Lord Momonosuke
when his emotions run high.

212
00:14:27.140 --> 00:14:28.220
Huh?

213
00:14:28.220 --> 00:14:31.810
Did you eat a devil fruit or something?

214
00:14:32.230 --> 00:14:34.690
Indeed, I did...

215
00:14:35.270 --> 00:14:39.730
<b>Guest Parlor

Inside the Castle</b>

216
00:14:45.070 --> 00:14:46.820
Speaking of Kaido...

217
00:14:47.660 --> 00:14:51.250
Back when the Marines
had him held captive...

218
00:14:53.250 --> 00:14:58.540
Vegapunk extracted Kaido's
hereditary elements...

219
00:14:58.540 --> 00:15:01.460
and used them to create
an artificial devil fruit.

220
00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:05.430
The government requested
that he hand over the fruit,

221
00:15:05.430 --> 00:15:09.390
but since Vegapunk
considered it a disappointing failure,

222
00:15:09.760 --> 00:15:13.060
it was stored at Punk Hazard long term.

223
00:15:14.980 --> 00:15:17.560
Why bring that up now?

224
00:15:17.560 --> 00:15:19.570
Punk Hazard was blown up.

225
00:15:19.570 --> 00:15:21.780
The fruit should be gone now.

226
00:15:21.780 --> 00:15:24.650
I can only hope it was
destroyed in that explosion,

227
00:15:25.320 --> 00:15:30.410
but Marine Branch G-5 reported
that one facility was still in operation...

228
00:15:34.660 --> 00:15:39.460
I'm just grateful... that it was a failure.

229
00:15:43.880 --> 00:15:48.220
"Treasury"

230
00:15:51.810 --> 00:15:53.680
Who treated our wounds?

231
00:15:54.220 --> 00:15:55.810
I do not know...

232
00:15:56.350 --> 00:15:58.730
But I believe I may have seen someone...

233
00:15:58.730 --> 00:16:01.110
No, it must have been a dream...

234
00:16:02.070 --> 00:16:04.780
After all, it could not have been...

235
00:16:07.610 --> 00:16:12.370
Sir Luffy and his allies are
engaging Kaido in our stead.

236
00:16:12.370 --> 00:16:15.750
We should not stay here and sit idly by!

237
00:16:16.290 --> 00:16:18.960
The battle for this island rages on!

238
00:16:18.960 --> 00:16:20.330
Let us move!

239
00:16:20.330 --> 00:16:23.710
We still have life left to give!

240
00:16:26.380 --> 00:16:27.970
You guys!

241
00:16:27.970 --> 00:16:30.590
You look like hell!

242
00:16:30.590 --> 00:16:32.720
How I've missed you all!

243
00:16:38.520 --> 00:16:41.270
You're so much older now!

244
00:16:49.360 --> 00:16:53.740
L-Lord Oden!

245
00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:57.120
Lord Oden?

246
00:17:01.210 --> 00:17:03.840
It's no wonder you're surprised!

247
00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:06.960
Toki sent me here to the future
with the help of her ability!

248
00:17:06.960 --> 00:17:08.720
I'll explain everything later.

249
00:17:08.720 --> 00:17:09.930
It's a long story!

250
00:17:10.680 --> 00:17:12.550
Lord Oden!

251
00:17:12.550 --> 00:17:14.260
So that is why you are here!

252
00:17:16.470 --> 00:17:18.640
Sorry for being late!

253
00:17:18.640 --> 00:17:22.850
But we don't have time to catch up right now!

254
00:17:24.570 --> 00:17:26.230
Now come!

255
00:17:26.230 --> 00:17:29.190
We go to Kaido, the man
we failed to kill on that fateful day!

256
00:17:30.240 --> 00:17:31.360
Of course!

257
00:17:31.360 --> 00:17:32.820
We are with you!

258
00:17:32.820 --> 00:17:34.950
That has been our wish from the beginning!

259
00:17:34.950 --> 00:17:36.490
Let us depart!

260
00:17:39.960 --> 00:17:43.250
I knew you guys would say that!

261
00:17:45.340 --> 00:17:46.710
Hold it, everyone!

262
00:17:47.920 --> 00:17:50.050
There's no way he's alive!

263
00:17:50.050 --> 00:17:52.010
He must be an impostor!

264
00:17:52.010 --> 00:17:54.180
What are you saying, Ashura?!

265
00:17:54.180 --> 00:17:55.050
Kin'emon!

266
00:17:56.930 --> 00:17:58.520
Remember Lady Toki's words!

267
00:17:58.640 --> 00:18:02.390
Travel to the past is impossible...

268
00:18:02.390 --> 00:18:04.650
but one can leap ahead to the future.

269
00:18:08.900 --> 00:18:11.860
"Travel to the past is impossible"!

270
00:18:12.280 --> 00:18:15.700
Lady Toki's ability was
to send people to the future!

271
00:18:15.700 --> 00:18:19.580
Lord Oden died that day!

272
00:18:19.580 --> 00:18:24.290
That fact would not change,
even in the future!

273
00:18:24.290 --> 00:18:28.210
No one can change the past!

274
00:18:30.550 --> 00:18:33.720
But... it could be him!

275
00:18:33.720 --> 00:18:34.760
I get that!

276
00:18:39.180 --> 00:18:40.600
But...!

277
00:18:45.480 --> 00:18:47.520
Snap out of it, Kin'emon!

278
00:18:52.150 --> 00:18:53.280
Look!

279
00:18:53.280 --> 00:18:55.280
He doesn't even bleed!

280
00:18:56.660 --> 00:18:57.700
Impossible!

281
00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:00.830
Ashura...

282
00:19:00.830 --> 00:19:05.170
I thought you had pledged to be my samurai.

283
00:19:07.750 --> 00:19:10.750
Be my samurai!

284
00:19:14.300 --> 00:19:15.380
Ashura!

285
00:19:17.720 --> 00:19:18.720
Ashura!

286
00:19:25.770 --> 00:19:29.480
Now you can see his true colors...

287
00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:33.570
I know we all feel the same...

288
00:19:33.570 --> 00:19:36.150
I wish he were real as well...

289
00:19:36.740 --> 00:19:39.950
But... this is an impostor!

290
00:19:39.950 --> 00:19:41.540
How terrible!

291
00:19:41.540 --> 00:19:44.620
Who could be posing as Lord Oden?!

292
00:19:44.620 --> 00:19:45.870
It's not really him?!

293
00:19:45.870 --> 00:19:47.210
Dammit!

294
00:19:52.880 --> 00:19:54.720
Are you okay, Ashura?!

295
00:19:55.880 --> 00:19:58.180
But... his demeanor...

296
00:19:58.590 --> 00:20:00.430
It is exactly like Oden's!

297
00:20:00.930 --> 00:20:03.470
The only one who could
mimic him so perfectly...

298
00:20:03.470 --> 00:20:04.730
is one of us!

299
00:20:05.230 --> 00:20:06.480
So it's you!

300
00:20:09.600 --> 00:20:12.650
Kanjuro!

301
00:20:14.650 --> 00:20:17.650
Don't be silly! I'm Oden!

302
00:20:19.110 --> 00:20:20.990
Ashura, forgive me!

303
00:20:20.990 --> 00:20:22.450
This is my fault!

304
00:20:22.830 --> 00:20:25.910
If I hadn't failed to finish off Kanjuro...

305
00:20:26.580 --> 00:20:31.000
Even the sharpest blade dulls
when turned on a friend...

306
00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:34.130
It must have been so hard on you...

307
00:20:38.090 --> 00:20:40.840
Is this a painting?
Where is your real body?!

308
00:20:43.390 --> 00:20:47.810
I am puppeteering Oden from afar!

309
00:20:47.810 --> 00:20:50.190
It's quite the exhausting task!

310
00:20:53.570 --> 00:20:54.820
Hey, Kiku!

311
00:20:55.150 --> 00:20:58.200
Your blade indeed found its mark!

312
00:20:58.200 --> 00:21:00.320
I am gravely wounded, as well!

313
00:21:00.320 --> 00:21:02.280
I expect this will be my final act!

314
00:21:02.700 --> 00:21:05.910
But the one thing that
keeps me pressing forward...

315
00:21:06.450 --> 00:21:08.910
is my grudge toward the Kozuki!

316
00:21:09.620 --> 00:21:12.040
Therefore, before I pass away...

317
00:21:12.040 --> 00:21:15.210
I will pierce through the heart
of the Kozuki Clan!

318
00:21:15.210 --> 00:21:17.840
As none other than Kurozumi Kanjuro!

319
00:21:25.310 --> 00:21:27.310
Lord Momonosuke is in danger!

320
00:21:27.310 --> 00:21:31.190
Oh, I seem to remember hearing
a voice from somewhere earlier...

321
00:21:31.190 --> 00:21:34.900
saying that Lord Momonosuke
is with a kunoichi...

322
00:21:35.230 --> 00:21:36.940
That must be Shinobu!

323
00:21:36.940 --> 00:21:39.240
Which means we can contact him!

324
00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:43.160
It's rather uncouth
to chase down a dying man.

325
00:21:47.290 --> 00:21:52.040
The Red Scabbards samurai will meet
their demise here, having achieved nothing!

326
00:21:54.330 --> 00:21:57.300
Myself included...

327
00:22:02.840 --> 00:22:05.800
Let's go out with a bang, shall we?

328
00:22:11.310 --> 00:22:12.810
You guys!

329
00:22:14.980 --> 00:22:18.730
You are my friends, are you not?

330
00:22:37.250 --> 00:22:38.840
Ashura!

331
00:22:38.840 --> 00:22:42.220
Get out of here, you guys!

332
00:22:45.550 --> 00:22:48.930
Go and stop Kanjuro!

333
00:22:49.260 --> 00:22:50.520
What are you doing?!

334
00:22:50.520 --> 00:22:52.480
Get off of me!

335
00:22:52.480 --> 00:22:55.100
Save Lord Momonosuke for me!

336
00:22:55.100 --> 00:22:57.730
We are in your debt, Ashura!

337
00:22:57.730 --> 00:22:59.480
You bastard!

338
00:22:59.480 --> 00:23:01.070
How dare you get in my way?!

339
00:23:02.490 --> 00:23:05.240
Damn you! Get off of me!

340
00:23:08.330 --> 00:23:13.660
You will never defile the memory
of Kozuki Oden ever again!

341
00:23:51.080 --> 00:23:54.250
Kanjuro!

342
00:23:58.330 --> 00:24:02.210
It's finally time for me, the star of
the show, to take center stage!

343
00:24:02.710 --> 00:24:04.840
First, I become a Kozuki...

344
00:24:04.840 --> 00:24:07.430
then, I eliminate the Kozuki...

345
00:24:07.430 --> 00:24:08.890
and finally, I die!

346
00:24:09.800 --> 00:24:13.260
This will be my grand finale!

347
00:24:13.260 --> 00:24:17.560
My life is one big, beautiful play!

348
00:24:34.450 --> 00:24:36.080
Jack!

349
00:24:36.450 --> 00:24:38.960
You bastard! Back for round two?!

350
00:24:39.500 --> 00:24:41.750
What a pain in the ass...

351
00:24:41.750 --> 00:24:44.170
These weaklings tried to stand in my way...

352
00:24:44.880 --> 00:24:48.470
all to protect their precious kings!

353
00:24:49.930 --> 00:24:53.890
Cat! Raizo! All of you, go on ahead!

354
00:24:55.350 --> 00:24:58.850
Everyone, save Lord Momonosuke for me!

355
00:24:59.230 --> 00:25:01.350
Let's go, Kin.

356
00:25:01.350 --> 00:25:02.690
Yeah...

357
00:25:02.690 --> 00:25:06.900
Be sure to catch up to us, Inuarashi!
We shall await your arrival!

358
00:25:13.620 --> 00:25:17.500
Do you intend to fight me all on
your own, Ruler of the Day?

359
00:25:17.500 --> 00:25:19.750
We're both injured.

360
00:25:19.750 --> 00:25:21.580
Seems like a fair fight.

361
00:25:22.000 --> 00:25:26.800
I didn't stay behind to settle an old grudge.

362
00:25:27.260 --> 00:25:33.720
If I let you run free, more people will
get hurt! And I can't allow that, Jack!

363
00:25:34.350 --> 00:25:36.770
There's no view of the moon from here!

364
00:25:36.770 --> 00:25:38.890
There's no poison gas, either!

365
00:25:43.060 --> 00:25:46.520
Well, then... Let's find out
who fate favors today.

366
00:26:02.250 --> 00:26:04.710
Hurry up and put it out!

367
00:26:05.710 --> 00:26:09.090
Water! We need more water!

368
00:26:22.600 --> 00:26:23.690
It's you...!

369
00:26:23.690 --> 00:26:27.230
It's time to teach you fools a lesson.

370
00:26:27.570 --> 00:26:29.820
I thought you were dead...

371
00:26:29.820 --> 00:26:32.070
How did you survive?!

372
00:26:41.540 --> 00:26:46.000
How could Kaido betray me like that?!

373
00:26:48.750 --> 00:26:51.050
There is no doubt about it, Lord Orochi...

374
00:26:51.050 --> 00:26:55.720
You were certainly beheaded
by Kaido... once, that is.

375
00:26:55.720 --> 00:26:56.890
However...

376
00:26:57.800 --> 00:26:59.930
I'm gonna burn it all down!

377
00:27:00.390 --> 00:27:04.890
Onigashima will be a raging inferno
by the time I'm through with it!

378
00:27:04.890 --> 00:27:07.520
There's nowhere to run in the air.

379
00:27:07.520 --> 00:27:09.690
All you can do is die!

380
00:27:13.070 --> 00:27:16.160
I'll kill every last one of them!

381
00:27:16.160 --> 00:27:18.950
They'll rue the day they crossed me!

382
00:27:30.380 --> 00:27:31.590
Momonosuke!

383
00:27:31.590 --> 00:27:33.800
Can you go back to normal?

384
00:27:33.800 --> 00:27:35.680
You stick out like a sore thumb.

385
00:27:35.680 --> 00:27:37.220
S-Sure...

386
00:27:43.850 --> 00:27:47.650
Stay put this time, Momonosuke!

387
00:27:47.650 --> 00:27:48.730
My apologies...

388
00:27:51.820 --> 00:27:55.360
It may not look it, but I have
learned to control it better...

389
00:27:56.740 --> 00:27:59.370
When I first met Luffy and the others,

390
00:27:59.370 --> 00:28:03.370
I would turn into a dragon
every time I got surprised or felt sad.

391
00:28:03.750 --> 00:28:05.000
Astonishing...

392
00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:07.330
I wonder if it's like my father's power...

393
00:28:07.330 --> 00:28:12.460
If I could turn into a monster like he does,
I would be of some help to everyone...

394
00:28:12.460 --> 00:28:16.050
Luffy is still fighting Kaido, right?

395
00:28:16.050 --> 00:28:17.680
I wonder if he's okay!

396
00:28:17.680 --> 00:28:20.640
I wanna take down Kaido too! As Oden!

397
00:28:20.640 --> 00:28:24.060
Luffy is growing much weaker...

398
00:28:24.060 --> 00:28:26.310
but somehow, he is in good spirits!

399
00:28:26.310 --> 00:28:27.560
Thank goodness...

400
00:28:28.810 --> 00:28:29.520
What?!

401
00:28:30.900 --> 00:28:33.940
How can you tell, Lord Momonosuke?!

402
00:28:40.990 --> 00:28:43.530
How do we beat these guys?

403
00:28:45.750 --> 00:28:49.040
They shrug off every attack
we throw at them...!

404
00:28:50.630 --> 00:28:53.960
That's a couple of Emperors for you...
They've got some thick skin.

405
00:28:53.960 --> 00:28:57.880
Can't they at least pretend it's making a dent?!

406
00:29:00.840 --> 00:29:01.970
It is working!

407
00:29:02.550 --> 00:29:05.850
After a beating like that,
there's no way they're not hurting!

408
00:29:05.850 --> 00:29:07.430
They're humans just like us!

409
00:29:07.980 --> 00:29:10.100
Gum-Gum...

410
00:29:16.190 --> 00:29:19.650
You already tried that earlier!
Think before you dive in!

411
00:29:20.280 --> 00:29:22.120
How can you call them human...

412
00:29:22.120 --> 00:29:24.700
when the gap between us is so big?

413
00:29:25.200 --> 00:29:28.910
Look, if you don't think we can win,
then why are you here?

414
00:29:28.910 --> 00:29:31.540
We're trying to figure out how to win!

415
00:29:32.210 --> 00:29:34.670
We should lure one of them away from here.

416
00:29:35.210 --> 00:29:36.630
Good idea.

417
00:29:36.630 --> 00:29:40.220
With the two of them side by side like this...

418
00:29:43.550 --> 00:29:46.760
it looks like we're in hell.

419
00:30:11.960 --> 00:30:13.790
Hell, huh?

420
00:30:13.790 --> 00:30:16.000
I've been there plenty of times.

421
00:30:17.340 --> 00:30:21.090
That light in your eyes never goes out...

422
00:30:23.970 --> 00:30:26.260
Straw Hat!

423
00:30:26.890 --> 00:30:28.720
We have the upper hand!
